    "diffSummary": "Implemented single-account login. zalo/login_profile maps types::Credentials into zca-rust (mapping kept inside the zalo layer so types stays zca-rust-free), logs in, and returns AccountProfile (own id via get_own_id + best-effort display name via fetch_account_info). command/login parses+validates the JSON payload at the boundary and returns only the non-secret AccountProfile. lib.rs registers the command. The frontend adds a Log in button that shows the account id/name. A live #[ignore] smoke (single_login_live) reads the gitignored .zalo-cred.json and performed a real login (uid_len=19, has_display_name=true); the attested stdout sidecar was scanned and contains no token values.",
    "changedFiles": [
        "src-tauri/src/command/mod.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/lib.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/zalo/mod.rs",
        "src/routes/+page.svelte"
    ],
